d nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=livia>Livia</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.galadriel.org/cgi-bin/showpic.cgi?j+luthien_ambrus+15" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#993300>(4/17/02 10:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm40.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.galadriel.org/cgi-bin/showpic.cgi?j+luthien_ambrus+15 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Livia rides to Chadesia</span><hr size=1> &quot; Mazon tam&quot; she said, fist to heart in a respectuous and friendly salutation, having learned some words in Amazon language from Myrene, a young priestess of Artemis in the Ephesian Artemision who was of Amazon blood and with whom she had befriended. <br>
<br>
In Ephesus, Myrene had been her only trusted friend and confident. But a night when she came in the forest, she heard a cry of distress. On the ground was lying her friend, badly wounded. In her last moment of consciousness, she described her murderors and Livia swore that justice would be made. The poor Myrene died in the Artemision, where her fellow priestesses and Livia had hopelessly tried to save her life.<br>
<br>
Myrene's murderors were three Roman soldiers, and one of them was the commander promised to Livia.<br>
<br>
But no Roman trusted Livia's words and there was no proof to accuse Myrene's murderors.<br>
<br>
Livia, to avoid her arranged marriage with this commander who was the murderor of her friend had fled far away.<br>
She wasn't able to talk or to see any of the Amazons without remembering the young priestess. Ashamed of being Roman.<br>
<br>
&quot; Thanks for your warm reception.My name is Livia Diana Tarquinia and my parents are Roman merchants from Ephesus.I fled from home after having been promised to a man I hate, and who have the blood of one of your sisters on his hands,Myrene, a young priestess of Artemis who was my best friend had been brutally murdered in the woods, close to the Artemision by three Roman soldiers, including the man promised to me. Unfortunately, there's no proof of his implication in this murder. Only the last words of his victim I've been the only to witness.I don't know what to do nor where to go and have no place to stay.I'm travelling alone, in no particular way and I'm sorry of entering in your lands,I don't know this territory and have no bad intention against your nation. My only demand, if it's not too audacious would be to be accepted in your tribe. I'm not a warrior and don't know much about your culture and traditions but I want to be the master of my life and learn your ways.To be an Amazon is what I ever wanted, and feel a deep connexion with Artemis that I can't explain, she guided me in my life, now my path sent me to Chadesia and I don't know if it's a simple hasard or my destiny&quot; <br>
<br>
She stopped her conversation, ashamed by her brashness, to make confidences to a queen, whom she didn't even know, like if it was a friend. She didn't knew the Amazon formal courtesies due to a Queen nor their traditions, only the Amazon salutation she had learned from Myrene.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uqueenvaria.showPublicProfile?language=EN>QueenVaria</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://hometown.aol.com/variaavande/images/tsianina2.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 440<br> <font color=#993300>(4/18/02 12:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm40.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://hometown.aol.com/cristalc15/images/varia3sm.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Livia rides to Chadesia</span><hr size=1> Varia listened to Livia tell her story, and couldn't help but feel bad for her. Of course she would have accepted her into the tribe anyway, but the woman's sad story just made her want to be more gentle than she normally was. Her bouncy personality would have to wait until she got to know Livia better. &quot;Of course you are welcome in my tribe,&quot; she said, nodding. &quot;And I am sorry for your losses,&quot; she added sincerely. <p><html> <center> <font face="vivaldi" size="+2" color="#ff0000"> ~Varia Angelina Avande~ </font> </html></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=livia>Livia</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.galadriel.org/cgi-bin/showpic.cgi?j+luthien_ambrus+15" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#993300>(4/18/02 6:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm40.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.galadriel.org/cgi-bin/showpic.cgi?j+luthien_ambrus+15 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Livia rides to Chadesia</span><hr size=1> After thanking her, Livia, in her respect and gratitude, kneeled in face of the queen, saying her: &quot; What I can do in exchange of your hospitality.&quot; Livia wanted to learn the culture of her new nation and the arts of battle, to break the bonds with her past of wealthy daughter of rich Roman merchants.<br>
<br>
She was missing Octavia, her mother, who loved her. But her father was very authoritarian and wanted to marry his daughter when a man of her class. But he didn't knew that the fiancé he had chose for his daughter was a murderor, blinded by the prestige this marriage to a military commander could have give to Livia. But Ephesus was no more her house. She would have wanted to become a virgin priestess of Artemis, in the Artemision of Ephesus.Maybe she would return, older, after learning her ways between the Amazons <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uqueenvaria.showPublicProfile?language=EN>QueenVaria</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://hometown.aol.com/variaavande/images/tsianina2.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 443<br> <font color=#993300>(4/18/02 7:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm40.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://hometown.aol.com/cristalc15/images/varia3sm.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Livia rides to Chadesia</span><hr size=1> ~Rise, child,~ Varia said gently. ~There is no need to kneel before me. You have shown your respect in the way you speak to me.~ She extended a hand to help Livia to her feet. ~All I ask for in exchange for my hospitality is loyalty.~ <p><html> <center> <font face="vivaldi" size="+2" color="#ff0000"> ~Varia Angelina Avande~ </font> </html></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=robin>Robin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#993300>(4/18/02 8:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezbo